BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_1_pt3
BaseField.Text: All staff shall have a working knowledge of the operating procedures.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4_pt2
BaseField.Text: Recruitment and selection of prospective employees,

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4_pt11
BaseField.Text: The orientation of staff to the agency's universal infection control procedures

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4_pt12
BaseField.Text: The code of ethical conduct shall prohibit employees and volunteers from engaging in sexual activity with individuals receiving services for a minimum of two (2) years after the last professional contact with the individual.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4_pt13
BaseField.Text: Providers shall also have a drug-free workplace policy for employees and prospective employees.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__a_
BaseField.Text: Records on all personnel shall be maintained.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__a_1_
BaseField.Text: The individual's current job description with minimum qualifications for the position and documentation that the staff meets the minimum qualifications outlined in the job description;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__a_4_pt1
BaseField.Text: A document signed and dated by the employee indicating that the employee

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__a_5_
BaseField.Text: A verified or certified copy of degrees, licenses, or certificates of each employee,

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__a_6_
BaseField.Text: Documentation of employee screening as required in paragraph (b); and,

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__a_7_
BaseField.Text: Documentation of required staff training (Inmate Substance Abuse Programs operated by the Department of Corrections are exempt from the provisions of this subparagraph).

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__c_hd
BaseField.Text: Employment History Checks and Checks of References.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_4__c_
BaseField.Text: The chief executive officer or designee, such as human resources staff, shall assess employment history checks and checks of references for each employee who has direct contact with children receiving services or adults who are intellectually disabled receiving services.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__a_pt1
BaseField.Text: All providers must develop overdose prevention plans.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__a_pt2
BaseField.Text: All staff must have a working knowledge of the overdose prevention plan.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__a_1_
BaseField.Text: Education about the risks of overdose, including having a lower tolerance for opioids if the individual is participating in an abstinence-based treatment program or is being discharged from a medication-assisted treatment program.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__a_2_
BaseField.Text: Information about Naloxone, the medication that reverses opioid overdose, including how to use Naloxone and where and how to access it.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__b_
BaseField.Text: Providers who maintain an emergency overdose prevention kit must develop and implement a plan to train staff in the prescribed use and the availability of the kit for use during all program hours of operation.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__c_
BaseField.Text: Overdose prevention information, as described in subparagraphs (22)(a)1. and 2. of this rule, must be shared with individuals upon admission.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_22__d_
BaseField.Text: Providers must offer overdose prevention information, as described in subparagraphs (22)(a)1. and 2. of this rule, to individuals placed on a waitlist to receive treatment services.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_5_pt1
BaseField.Text: Education of staff in the importance of the grievance system

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_5_pt2
BaseField.Text: Education of staff in the importance of individual rights;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_6_
BaseField.Text: Specific levels of appeal with corresponding time frames for resolution;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_7_
BaseField.Text: Timely receipt of a filed grievance;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_8_
BaseField.Text: The logging and tracking of filed grievances until resolved or concluded by actions of the provider's governing board;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_9_
BaseField.Text: Written notification of the decision to the appellant; and

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_10_
BaseField.Text: Analysis of trends to identify opportunities for improvement.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_
BaseField.Text: Within six (6) months of the hiring date, employees must complete the following trainings:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_1_
BaseField.Text: A two (2) hour educational course on HIV/AIDS as required by section 381.0035, F.S.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_2_
BaseField.Text: Overdose prevention training which must be renewed biennially. The training shall include, at a minimum, information about:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_2_c_
BaseField.Text: Naloxone, the medication that reverses opioid overdose, including how to use Naloxone and the importance of individuals at risk of opioid overdose and their friends and family having access to Naloxone.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_3_pt1
BaseField.Text: Training in incident reporting procedures and requirements in accordance with subsection 65D-30.004(17), F.A.C., the affirmative duty requirements

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_3_pt2
BaseField.Text: Training in the affirmative duty requirements and protections of chapter 415, F.S.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_3_pt3
BaseField.Text: Training in Title V of the Americans with Disabilities Act.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_4_pt1
BaseField.Text: For direct care staff working in component services identified in subsection 65D-30.004(12), F.A.C.,

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_4_pt2
BaseField.Text: two (2) hours of training in verbal de-escalation techniques

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_5_
BaseField.Text: Staff performing nursing support functions must be trained in those services prior to performing that function.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_6_
BaseField.Text: For all direct care staff, training and certification in cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) and first aid. Staff must maintain CPR and first aid certification, and a copy of the valid certificate must be filed in the personnel record.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_pt1
BaseField.Text: All staff and volunteers who provide direct care or prevention services shall participate in a minimum of 10 hours of documented training per year related to their duties and responsibilities.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_pt2
BaseField.Text: This includes training conducted annually in the following areas:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_1_
BaseField.Text: Prevention and control of infection in inpatient and residential settings;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_2_
BaseField.Text: Fire prevention, life safety, and disaster preparedness;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_5_
BaseField.Text: Federal law, 42 CFR, Part 2, and sections 397.334(10), 397.501(7), 397.752, F.S. applicable state laws regarding confidentiality.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__e_
BaseField.Text: In instances where an individual has received the requisite training as required in paragraphs (1)(c) and (d) during the year prior to employment by a provider, that individual will have met the training requirements. This provision applies only if the individual is able to produce documentation that the training was completed and that such training was provided by persons who or organizations that are qualified to provide such training

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__f_hd
BaseField.Text: Special Training Requirements for Clinical Staff.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__f_
BaseField.Text: All new clinical staff who work at least 20 hours per week or more must receive 12 hours of competency-based training related to substance use disorder treatment and recovery within the first year.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__g_
BaseField.Text: In addition to paragraphs (1)(c) and (d), new staff providing prevention services shall receive 12 hours basic training in science-based prevention within the first year of employment.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__h_
BaseField.Text: Training is required before personnel may supervise the self-administration of medication.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__h_pt1
BaseField.Text: At least two and a half (2.5) hours of training is required which may be conducted only by licensed practical nurses, licensed registered nurses or advanced practice registered nurses.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__h_pt2
BaseField.Text: Personnel responsible for training must certify by signed document or certificate the competency of unlicensed staff to supervise the self-administration of medication.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__h_pt3
BaseField.Text: Proof of training shall be documented in the personnel file and shall be completed prior to implementing the supervision of self-administration of medication.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_
BaseField.Text: In addition to the requirements of paragraph (h), self-administration of medication training must include step-by-step procedures, covering, at a minimum, the following subjects:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_1_
BaseField.Text: Safe storage, handling, and disposal of medications;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_2_
BaseField.Text: Comprehensive understanding of and compliance with medication instructions on a prescription label, a healthcare practitioner's order, and proper completion of medication observation record (MOR) form;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_3_
BaseField.Text: The medical indications and purposes for commonly used medications, their common side effects, and symptoms of adverse reactions;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_4_
BaseField.Text: The proper administration of oral, transdermal, ophthalmic, otic, rectal, inhaled or topical medications;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_5_
BaseField.Text: Safety and sanitation practices while administering medication;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_6_
BaseField.Text: Medication administration documentation and record keeping requirements;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_7_
BaseField.Text: Medical errors and medical error reporting;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_8_
BaseField.Text: Determinations of need for medication administration assistance and informed consent requirements;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__i_9_
BaseField.Text: Procedural arrangements for individuals who require medication offsite; and

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4_
BaseField.Text: Staff must provide services within the scope of their professional licensure certification; or training and competence in applicable clinical protocols.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__a_
BaseField.Text: The scope of practice limitations listed in subsection (3) apply to the following unlicensed staff who must work directly under the supervision of a qualified professional:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__a_1_
BaseField.Text: Bachelor's or master's degree level practitioners. Practitioners must hold a degree from an accredited university or college with a major in counseling, social work, psychology, nursing, rehabilitation, special education, health education, or a related human services field;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__a_2_
BaseField.Text: Registered marriage and family therapy, clinical social work, and mental health counseling interns;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__a_3_
BaseField.Text: Certified master's degree level addiction professionals who are certified by the Florida Certification Board;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__a_4_
BaseField.Text: Certified addictions professionals who are certified by the Florida Certification Board;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__a_5_
BaseField.Text: Certified addiction counselors who are certified by the Florida Certification Board.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__b_pt1
BaseField.Text: Certified recovery peer specialists and specialist or certified recovery support specialists who are certified by the Florida Certification Board may provide all services listed in subsection (3) of this rule, except counseling listed in paragraph (3)(l), under the supervision of a qualified professional or a certified recovery peer specialist with a minimum of three (3) years of experience providing recovery support services to individuals with substance use disorders.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_4__b_pt2
BaseField.Text: Recovery support specialists and recovery peer specialists are allowed one year from the date of their employment to obtain certification through the Florida Certification Board.

BaseField.Name: CIT_397_4073_2_hd
BaseField.Text: Employment History Checks; Checks of References

BaseField.Name: CIT_397_4073_2_pt2
BaseField.Text: employment history checks for all owners, directors, chief financial officers, and clinical supervisors

BaseField.Name: CIT_397_4073_2_pt3
BaseField.Text: checks of references for all owners, directors, chief financial officers, and clinical supervisors

BaseField.Name: CIT_397_4073_2_pt4
BaseField.Text: directors shall assess employment history checks and checks of references
